gamemodeoverhaul.configgui.enablegmcomma: Set this to false if you don't want the mod to add the '/gm' command
gamemodeoverhaul.configgui.enablereallys: Set this to false if you don't the mod to add '/gmc', '/gms', '/gmsp' and '/gma'
gamemodeoverhaul.configgui.enabledgmcomm: Set this to false if you don't want the mod to add the '/dgm' command
gamemodeoverhaul.configgui.enabledifficu: Set this to false if you don't want the mod to add the integer valuse for '/difficulty'
gamemodeoverhaul.configgui.enablekill: Set this to false if you want to have '/kill' require an entity argument
gamemodeoverhaul.configgui.enabletoggled: Set this to false if you don't want to have the mod add '/toggledownfall' back
gamemodeoverhaul.configgui.enablexp: Set this to false if you don't want to have the mod add '/xp <number>[L]' back
gamemodeoverhaul.configgui.setXPStringVa: Set this to whatever you want '/[THIS] <number[L]>' to be. It CANNOT be 'xp' due to limitations in Minecraft.
gamemodeoverhaul.configgui.enablewelcome: Set this to false if you don't want the welcome message
gamemodeoverhaul.configgui.enabledebugme: Set this to true if you want GamemodeOverhaul to log debug messages
